Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later). Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel @Red Onion{1} and cut into ½-inch-thick rounds. Slice @Roma Tomato{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Halve @Lime{1}. Halve @Brioche Buns{2}.

== Bacon & Onions ==

Place onion on one side of a second baking sheet; drizzle with @olive oil{2%teaspoons} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove sheet from oven. Place @Bacon{4%ounce} on empty side; sprinkle with @Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon}, pepper, and a pinch of @Chipotle Powder{1%teaspoon}. Return to oven until bacon is caramelized and onion is lightly charred, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on the bacon—thinner pieces will cook more quickly and thicker pieces may take a bit longer.

== Special Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Ketchup{2%tablespoon}, and half the @Mustard Seeds{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in a pinch of remaining chipotle powder to taste.

== Patties ==

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. In a #medium bowl{}, mix @Ground Beef{10%ounce} with remaining mustard seeds and Fry Seasoning. Form into patties; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add patties to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with @Pepper Jack Cheese{½%cup}(jalapeño-flecked); cover pan until cheese melts.

== Assembly ==

Toast buns until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Spread with a layer of sauce, then fill with patties, as much tomato and onion as you like, and bacon.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, @Pepitas{½%ounce}, and any remaining tomato and onion with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and lime juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide burgers, salad, and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining sauce on the side for dipping.